===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|hamelet|lang=fro}}, diminutive of {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|hamel|lang=fro}} (Modern French {{term|hameau|lang=fr}}), in turn diminutive of {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|ham|lang=fro}}, of {{etyl|gem|en}} origin. Cognates include {{m|en|home}}, Dutch {{m|nl|heem}}, German {{m|de|Heim}}, Old English {{m|ang|hām}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A small [[village]] or a group of houses.
# {{context|British|lang=en}} A village that does not have its own [[church]].
# Any of the fish of the genus {{taxlink|Hypoplectrus|genus|noshow=1}} in the family [[Serranidae]].

